
##HowTo Markdown

##I. Pandoc command options 

* --chapters => Treat top-Level headers as chapters in Latex, Contexts and 
   docbook

* --latex-engine=pdflatex|lualatex|xelatex Use the specified LaTeX engine
when producing PDF output. The default is pdflatex. If the engine is not in
your PATH, the full path of the engine may be specified here.


* --bibliography=FILE Set the bibliography field in the document’s metadata 
to FILE, overriding any value set in the metadata, and process citations 
using pandoc-citeproc. (This is equivalent to --metadata bibliography=FILE
--filter pandoc-citeproc.)
* --csl=FILE Set the csl field in the document’s metadata to FILE, overriding
any value set in the metadata. (This is equivalent to --metadata csl=FILE.)
* --citation-abbreviations=FILE Set the citation-abbreviations field in the
document’s metadata to FILE, overriding any value set in the metadata. (This
is equivalent to --metadata citation-abbreviations=FILE.)

